    "minides": "Volkswagen's third-generation Tiguan, offered exclusively in India in its sportiest R-Line trim — featuring a 15-inch touchscreen, Level 2 ADAS, DCC Pro adaptive suspension, 4MOTION AWD, and 9 airbags.",
    "description": "The third-generation Volkswagen Tiguan launched in India in 2025 in a single fully-loaded R-Line variant at ₹47.11 lakh (ex-showroom). It is powered by a 2.0-litre TSI EVO turbocharged petrol engine producing 204 PS and 320 Nm, paired with a 7-speed DSG and intelligent 4MOTION all-wheel drive. The R-Line brings sporty bumpers front and rear, a connected full-width light bar at the front, gloss-black detailing, 19-inch dual-tone alloy wheels, and 'R' badging throughout. Inside, the cabin features a 15-inch touchscreen with wireless Android Auto and Apple CarPlay, a 10.2-inch digital driver display, a head-up display, panoramic sunroof, DCC Pro adaptive chassis control, massage front seats, configurable ambient lighting, and a full Level 2 ADAS suite including Travel Assist. The Tiguan R-Line holds a 5-star Euro NCAP safety rating and comes with 9 airbags as standard."
  },
